===Etymology===
From {{etyl|NL.|en}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|ῥάχις||spine, ridge|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɹeɪkɪs/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|rachises|pl2=rachides}}

# {{botany}} The main [[shaft]] of either a [[compound]] [[leaf]], [[head]] of [[grain]], or fern [[frond]].
# {{zoology|anatomy}} The [[spine]] or the [[vertebrae]] of the spine.
# {{ornithology}} The [[central]] shaft of a [[feather]].

====Usage notes====
* The plural form {{term|rachides}} is technically erroneous, being based on a mistaken impression of the Ancient Greek stem.

